Year = {{2013}},
Volume = {{21}},
Pages = {1020-1029},
Abstract = {{We present absolute line center frequencies for 24 fundamental nu(3)
   ro-vibrational P-branch transitions near 4.5 mu m in N2O with an
   absolute expanded (multiplied by 2) frequency uncertainty of 800 kHz.
   The spectra are acquired with a swept laser spectrometer consisting of
   an external-cavity quantum cascade laser whose instantaneous frequency
   is continuously tracked against a near-infrared frequency comb. The
   measured absorbance profiles have a well-calibrated frequency axis, and
   are fitted to determine absolute line center values. We discuss the main
   sources of uncertainty.}},
